# ---------------- Database ----------------
# db.sqlite3 holds real user accounts (emails, password hashes), health
# session data, device keys, and consent records — this is exactly the kind
# of medical/PII data the rest of this project's security model exists to
# protect, so it must never be committed. (It was previously tracked
# intentionally as a "dev DB" — that was a mistake once real user signups
# started landing in it; removed via `git rm --cached` and gitignored here.
# See SECURITY_NOTE.md for what to do about the already-pushed history.)
database/*.sqlite3
database/*.sqlite3-journal
database/*.sqlite3-wal
database/*.sqlite3-shm

# ---------------- Logs ----------------
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# ---------------- HRV model system ----------------
# Raw wearable datasets and trained model artifacts are large/binary and
# environment-specific; they should never be committed. Point HRV_MODEL_DIR
# (see docs/HRV_INTEGRATION.md) at wherever a real checkpoint lives locally.
HRV */personalized_hrv_system/Dataset3/
HRV */personalized_hrv_system/**/outputs/
HRV */personalized_hrv_system/**/checkpoints/
HRV */personalized_hrv_system/**/*.pt
HRV */personalized_hrv_system/**/*.joblib
HRV */personalized_hrv_system/**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
